course.
"Did
Mr.
Moore
tell
you
to
say
that?"
"Certainly;
why
not?
And
now,
do
come,
and
let
us
once
more
be
as
we
were
at
Sympson
Grove.
We
used
to
have
pleasant
school
hours
in
those
days."
Miss
Keeldar
perhaps
thought
that
circumstances
were
changed
since
then;
however,
she
made
no
